= Document Attributes

Document attributes allow you to define reusable values and configuration.

== Basic Attributes

:author: John Doe
:version: 1.0
:date: 2024-01-01

Written by {author}, version {version}, dated {date}.

== Attribute Examples

:product-name: Remarkd
:product-version: 2.0
:company: Example Corp

Welcome to {product-name} version {product-version} by {company}.

== Boolean Attributes

:toc:
:icons: font
:sectnums:

Table of contents, icons, and section numbering are enabled.

== Attribute Substitution

:url-home: https://example.com
:url-docs: https://docs.example.com

Visit {url-home} for the homepage.

Check {url-docs} for documentation.

== Conditional Attributes

ifeval::[version >= 2.0]
This content appears for version 2.0 and above.
endif::[]

== Attribute Examples

:api-url: https://api.example.com
:api-version: v2

API endpoint: {api-url}/{api-version}/users

== Multiple Attributes

:first-name: John
:last-name: Doe
:email: john@example.com

Contact: {first-name} {last-name} <{email}>

== Attribute in Lists

:item1: First item
:item2: Second item
:item3: Third item

* {item1}
* {item2}
* {item3}

== Complex Attributes

:base-url: https://example.com
:api-path: /api/v1
:endpoint: /users

Full URL: {base-url}{api-path}{endpoint}


